Why not?

152
00:09:01,142 --> 00:09:05,009
Why couldn't one single person
acknowledge my strength?

153
00:09:05,042 --> 00:09:06,742
Why, Iruka?

154
00:09:06,776 --> 00:09:09,342
It's not fair when
you even acknowledge

155
00:09:09,376 --> 00:09:11,709
that Nine-Tailed brat Naruto!

156
00:09:11,742 --> 00:09:14,042
What about me?

157
00:09:14,076 --> 00:09:16,042
-It's still not
too late, Mizuki.

158
00:09:16,076 --> 00:09:18,976
If you pay for your
crimes, you can start anew.

159
00:09:19,009 --> 00:09:21,742
The people of the village,
I promise they'll forgive--

160
00:09:21,776 --> 00:09:23,076
-Don't make me laugh!

161
00:09:23,109 --> 00:09:27,109
What gives you the right to
stand there and lecture me?

162
00:09:27,142 --> 00:09:29,576
You're just the same
as the rest of them.

163
00:09:29,609 --> 00:09:33,409
Treating me like I'm
not as good as you.

164
00:09:33,442 --> 00:09:34,109
-Mizuki--

165
00:09:34,142 --> 00:09:35,309
-That day.

166
00:09:35,342 --> 00:09:36,776
Yes.

167
00:09:36,809 --> 00:09:38,709
Everything began on that day.

168
00:09:43,876 --> 00:09:45,309
[sigh]

169
00:09:45,342 --> 00:09:48,776
-You know, no point
getting nervous like that.

170
00:09:48,809 --> 00:09:50,176
-Mizuki.

171
00:09:50,209 --> 00:09:51,676
-Tomorrow's the big day.

172
00:09:51,709 --> 00:09:54,809
The Ninja Academy's
teacher recruitment exam.

173
00:09:54,842 --> 00:09:55,609
-Yeah.

174
00:09:55,642 --> 00:09:57,276
The suspense is killing me.

175
00:09:57,309 --> 00:09:59,309
I'm so jealous of you.

176
00:09:59,342 --> 00:10:01,176
Your scores are so
high, you'll probably

177
00:10:01,209 --> 00:10:04,976
breeze right through
tomorrow's exam.

178
00:10:05,009 --> 00:10:06,742
-I don't know about that.

179
00:10:06,776 --> 00:10:09,376
Hey, in any case,
let's do our best.

180
00:10:09,409 --> 00:10:09,876
-Yeah.

181
00:10:23,242 --> 00:10:24,176
Oh no!

182
00:10:32,609 --> 00:10:34,542
-Get down!

183
00:10:34,576 --> 00:10:38,009
That was a close one, Iruka.

184
00:10:38,042 --> 00:10:39,042
-Yeah.

185
00:10:39,076 --> 00:10:40,676
Mizuki, thank you.

186
00:10:40,709 --> 00:10:42,009
You saved me.

187
00:10:42,042 --> 00:10:43,409
-Don't worry about it.

188
00:10:43,442 --> 00:10:44,742
Now, let's get going.

189
00:10:56,609 --> 00:10:58,609
-I did it.

190
00:10:58,642 --> 00:11:01,442
I did it!

191
00:11:01,476 --> 00:11:01,942
Mizuki!

192
00:11:06,309 --> 00:11:09,676
MAN: Now, regarding Mizuki--
I say we adopt a wait

193
00:11:09,709 --> 00:11:11,342
and see attitude.

194
00:11:11,376 --> 00:11:12,109
MAN: Yes.

195
00:11:12,142 --> 00:11:15,509
It's a shame, but I agree.

196
00:11:15,542 --> 00:11:17,842
There are still many
questions about his mission

197
00:11:17,876 --> 00:11:19,776
to recover the
secret manuscript,

198
00:11:19,809 --> 00:11:22,809
and well, until
those are cleared up,

199
00:11:22,842 --> 00:11:24,209
he shouldn't progress.

200
00:11:24,242 --> 00:11:28,476
-According to the autopsy of the
fallen man, the cause of death

201
00:11:28,509 --> 00:11:30,042
was suffocation.

202
00:11:30,076 --> 00:11:33,009
And yet, in Mizuki and
the others' report,

203
00:11:33,042 --> 00:11:36,276
they stated his leg injury
wasn't that serious.

204
00:11:36,309 --> 00:11:37,276
-Yes.

205
00:11:37,309 --> 00:11:39,709
I understand.

206
00:11:39,742 --> 00:11:42,309
He's brilliant, but
he must be held back.

207
00:11:42,342 --> 00:11:42,809
-Damn!

208
00:11:46,509 --> 00:11:47,976
You see?

209
00:11:48,009 --> 00:11:49,909
I was just carrying
out the mission

210
00:11:49,942 --> 00:11:51,642
I was assigned to complete.

211
00:11:51,676 --> 00:11:56,042
You've no idea how miserable my
life has been since that day.

212
00:11:56,076 --> 00:11:58,909
Since then, I--
Don't you understand?

213
00:12:01,476 --> 00:12:02,876
You don't know.

214
00:12:02,909 --> 00:12:05,509
You have no idea!

215
00:12:05,542 --> 00:12:09,276
I've been through so much pain,
and you've had it so easy.

216
00:12:09,309 --> 00:12:12,142
Which one of us is
the true shinobi?

217
00:12:12,176 --> 00:12:14,176
Let's find out, shall we?

218
00:12:23,753 --> 00:12:25,453
Come, Iruka.

219
00:12:25,486 --> 00:12:26,453
Come on in.

220
00:12:31,119 --> 00:12:32,319
-Darn it.

221
00:12:32,353 --> 00:12:34,519
-Mizuki, where are you hiding?

222
00:12:34,553 --> 00:12:37,053
You don't have any intention
of changing your evil ways,

223
00:12:37,086 --> 00:12:38,253
do you?

224
00:12:38,286 --> 00:12:41,819
-Don't make me say the
same thing over and over.

225
00:12:41,853 --> 00:12:43,719
-Then I'll bring this to an end.

226
00:12:43,753 --> 00:12:44,719
